'From Squeak2.8alpha of 4 February 2000 [latest update: #2210] on 1 June 2000 at 1:06:10 pm'!"Change Set:		099QuoFix-srDate:			28 May 2000Author:			Stephan RudlofException raised by division by zero, improved code, comment."!!SmallInteger methodsFor: 'arithmetic' stamp: 'sr 5/28/2000 04:41'!quo: aNumber 	"Primitive. Divide the receiver by the argument and answer with the 	result. Round the result down towards zero to make it a whole integer. 	Fail if the argument is 0 or is not a SmallInteger. Optional. See Object 	documentation whatIsAPrimitive."	<primitive: 13>	aNumber = 0 ifTrue: [^ (ZeroDivide dividend: self) signal].	(aNumber isMemberOf: SmallInteger)		ifFalse: [^ super quo: aNumber].	(aNumber == -1 and: [self == self class minVal])		ifTrue: ["result is aLargeInteger" ^ self negated].	self primitiveFailed! !